---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const docsHref = `${base}/docs/getting-started`;
const repoHref = 'https://github.com/Nikoro/spellbook';
const ogImage = `${base}/og.png`;
const canonical = `https://nikoro.github.io${base}/`;
const title = 'Spellbook — Cast commands like spells. No prefix.';
const description =
  'Spellbook is a macOS-first native Swift CLI that turns project commands into real shell commands — no `make`, `just`, or `npm run` prefix. Type-safe params, switches, inheritance, doctor diagnostics, zero runtime dependencies.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonical} />
    <link rel="icon" href={`${base}/favicon.ico`} />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href={`${base}/icon.png`} />

    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:image" content={`https://nikoro.github.io${base}/og.png`} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={canonical} />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content={`https://nikoro.github.io${base}/og.png`} />

    <link
      rel="preconnect"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"
    />
    <link
      rel="preconnect"
      href="https://fonts.gstatic.com"
      crossorigin
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a href={base + '/'} class="brand" aria-label="Spellbook home">
        <picture>
          <source srcset={`${base}/icon.webp`} type="image/webp" />
          <img class="brand__icon" src={`${base}/icon.png`} alt="" width="32" height="32" />
        </picture>
        <span class="brand__name">Spellbook</span>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary">
        <a href={docsHref}>Docs</a>
        <a href={`${base}/changelog`}>Changelog</a>
        <a href={repoHref} rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero__text">
          <picture class="hero__wordmark">
            <source srcset={`${base}/wordmark.webp`} type="image/webp" />
            <img
              src={`${base}/wordmark.png`}
              alt="Spellbook"
              width="480"
              height="200"
            />
          </picture>
          <p class="hero__tagline">
            Cast commands like spells.<br />
            <span class="hero__tagline-accent">No prefix:</span>
          </p>
          <div class="hero__no-prefix" aria-label="Comparison with other task runners">
            <ul class="hero__strikes">
              <li><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">❌</span>make hello</li>
              <li><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">❌</span>just hello</li>
              <li><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">❌</span>npm run hello</li>
              <li><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">❌</span>task hello</li>
              <li><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">❌</span>./scripts/hello.sh</li>
              <li class="hero__win"><span class="hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">✅</span><code>hello</code></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__media" role="img" aria-label="Spellbook demo showing a spells.yaml manifest and terminal output">
          <div class="demo-window" data-demo-window data-demo-step="1" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="demo-window__bar">
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
              <span></span>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-pane demo-pane--editor">
              <div class="demo-pane__title">spells.yaml</div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="1">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>: echo "Hello World"</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="2">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>:
  <span class="key">script</span>: echo "Hello &#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;"
  <span class="key">params</span>:
    <span class="key">required</span>:
      <span class="key">name</span>:</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="3">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>:
  <span class="key">script</span>: echo "Hello &#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;"
  <span class="key">params</span>:
    <span class="key">required</span>:
      <span class="key">name</span>:
        <span class="key">flags</span>: -n, --name</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="4">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>:
  <span class="key">script</span>: echo "Hello &#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;"
  <span class="key">params</span>:
    <span class="key">optional</span>:
      <span class="key">name</span>:
        <span class="key">flags</span>: -n, --name
        <span class="key">default</span>: John</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="5">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>:
  <span class="key">script</span>: echo "Hello &#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;"
  <span class="key">params</span>:
    <span class="key">required</span>:
      <span class="key">name</span>:
        <span class="key">values</span>: [Bob, Ann, John]</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--yaml" data-yaml-step="6">
                <pre><code><span class="key">hello</span>: <span class="comment">## Greet someone by name</span>
  <span class="key">script</span>: echo "Hello &#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;"
  <span class="key">params</span>:
    <span class="key">optional</span>:
      <span class="key">name</span>: <span class="comment">## Person to greet</span>
        <span class="key">flags</span>: -n, --name
        <span class="key">default</span>: World</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-pane demo-pane--terminal">
              <div class="demo-pane__title">terminal</div>
              <div class="demo-code demo-code--terminal">
                <pre><code data-demo-terminal><span class="prompt">$</span> <span class="typed">hello</span><span class="cursor"></span></code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="install" aria-label="Install Spellbook">
        <div class="install__cta">
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href={docsHref}>
            <span class="btn__label">Get Started</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="install-bar" data-method="curl">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="install-bar__trigger"
            id="install-trigger"
            aria-haspopup="listbox"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controls="install-menu"
          >
            <span class="install-bar__method-label" data-install-label>curl</span>
            <svg class="install-bar__chevron" width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 4.5l3 3 3-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="install-bar__cmd-btn" id="install-copy" aria-label="Copy install command">
            <code class="install-bar__cmd" id="install-cmd" data-install-cmd>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nikoro/spellbook/main/install.sh | sh</code>
            <span class="install-bar__hint" data-install-bar-hint hidden>The picker, atomic activation, and shell integration — wired up step-by-step below ↓</span>
            <span class="install-bar__copy-icon" data-copy-icon aria-hidden="true">
              <svg class="icon-copy" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 18 18">
                <rect x="4" y="4" width="9" height="9" rx="1.6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <rect x="6.5" y="6.5" width="9" height="9" rx="1.6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              </svg>
              <svg class="icon-check" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 18 18">
                <path d="M3.5 9.5l3.8 3.8L14.5 5.7" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </button>

          <ul
            class="install-bar__menu"
            id="install-menu"
            role="listbox"
            aria-labelledby="install-trigger"
            hidden
          >
            <li role="option" data-method="curl" aria-selected="true">
              <span class="install-bar__menu-key">curl</span>
              <span class="install-bar__menu-desc">macOS · one-liner installer with shell-integration prompt</span>
            </li>
            <li role="option" data-method="brew" aria-selected="false">
              <span class="install-bar__menu-key">Homebrew</span>
              <span class="install-bar__menu-desc">macOS · <code>brew install nikoro/tap/spellbook</code></span>
            </li>
            <li role="option" data-method="manual" aria-selected="false">
              <span class="install-bar__menu-key">Manual</span>
              <span class="install-bar__menu-desc">Step-by-step download &amp; wiring</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Hint shown for curl/brew (default-visible). Text is swapped per method by wireInstallBar(). -->
        <p class="install__hint" data-install-hint>
          macOS only. The curl installer auto-detects your shell (zsh / bash / fish), checks <code>~/.local/bin</code> on <code>$PATH</code>, and prompts before adding the integration to your rc file.
        </p>

        <!-- Step-by-step manual instructions (toggle from dropdown) -->
        <div class="install__manual" data-install-manual hidden>
          <ol class="manual-steps">
            <li>
              <h4>1 · Download the binary</h4>
              <p>Pick the asset that matches your CPU (<code>arm64</code> for Apple Silicon, <code>x86_64</code> for Intel) from <a href="https://github.com/Nikoro/spellbook/releases/latest" rel="noopener">the latest GitHub Release</a>.</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`ARCH=$(uname -m)   # arm64 or x86_64
curl -fsSL -o /tmp/spells \\
  https://github.com/Nikoro/spellbook/releases/latest/download/spells-macos-$ARCH`}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <h4>2 · Verify the checksum</h4>
              <p>Each release ships a <code>.sha256</code> sidecar. Match it before running anything.</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`curl -fsSL -o /tmp/spells.sha256 \\
  https://github.com/Nikoro/spellbook/releases/latest/download/spells-macos-$ARCH.sha256
shasum -a 256 -c <(awk -v f=/tmp/spells '{print $1"  "f}' /tmp/spells.sha256)`}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <h4>3 · Install and make executable</h4>
              <p>Drop the binary somewhere on your <code>$PATH</code>. The curl installer uses <code>~/.local/bin</code>.</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`mkdir -p ~/.local/bin
mv /tmp/spells ~/.local/bin/spells
chmod +x ~/.local/bin/spells`}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <h4>4 · Add <code>~/.local/bin</code> to <code>$PATH</code> (if missing)</h4>
              <p>Skip if it's already there. <code>echo $PATH | tr ':' '\n' | grep .local/bin</code> to check.</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc</span>
                <pre><code>export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">~/.config/fish/config.fish</span>
                <pre><code>set -gx PATH $HOME/.local/bin $PATH</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <h4>5 · Wire up shell integration (TAB completion + wrapper PATH)</h4>
              <p>This is what gives you the picker on TAB and adds <code>~/.spellbook/bin</code> to <code>$PATH</code>.</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc</span>
                <pre><code>{`# spellbook
eval "$(spells init zsh)"   # or bash`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">~/.config/fish/config.fish</span>
                <pre><code>spells init fish | source</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li>
              <h4>6 · Verify</h4>
              <p>Open a new shell, then check the install + path integration:</p>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`spells --version
spells doctor   # checks PATH, manifest, wrapper state, shell integration`}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="comparison" aria-label="Comparison">
        <h2>How Spellbook fixes what you already use</h2>
        <div class="compare-stack">
          <article class="compare-row">
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--bad">
              <h3>Shell alias</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">~/.zshrc</span>
                <pre><code>alias deploy='./scripts/deploy.sh staging'</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>$ deploy
# works on your machine only</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="cons">
                <li><strong>Not in the repo.</strong><span>Lives in <code>~/.zshrc</code>, teammates and CI never see it.</span></li>
                <li><strong>No params, no validation.</strong><span>Pass garbage, the script gets garbage.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Breaks on branches.</strong><span>Need <code>staging</code> vs <code>production</code>? Welcome to <code>deploy-staging</code>, <code>deploy-prod</code>…</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--good">
              <h3>Spellbook</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml</span>
                <pre><code>{`deploy:
  switch:
    staging:    ./deploy.sh staging
    production: ./deploy.sh production
  default: staging`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`$ deploy             # default → staging
$ deploy production  # explicit branch
$ spells list        # discoverable`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="pros">
                <li><strong>Lives with the repo.</strong><span>Committed in <code>spells.yaml</code> — works for every teammate, CI, every machine.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Branches built-in.</strong><span><code>switch:</code> with picker, defaults, and TAB completion — no <code>deploy-*</code> proliferation.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Discoverable.</strong><span><code>spells list</code> shows everything. <code>spells help deploy</code> shows args.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="compare-row">
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--bad">
              <h3>Makefile</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">Makefile</span>
                <pre><code>{`deploy:
\t./scripts/deploy.sh staging`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>$ make deploy ENV=staging</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="cons">
                <li><strong>Prefix tax.</strong><span>Always <code>make deploy</code> — five extra keystrokes, every time.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Wrong tool for shell scripts.</strong><span>Tabs-vs-spaces, <code>.PHONY</code> ceremony, recursive-make footguns.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Stringly-typed.</strong><span>No types, no enums, no named flags — just <code>VAR=value</code>.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--good">
              <h3>Spellbook</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml</span>
                <pre><code>{`deploy:
  params:
    env:
      values: [staging, production]
  script: ./deploy.sh {{env}}`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>{`$ deploy staging   # validated enum
$ deploy prod      # error: invalid value`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="pros">
                <li><strong>No prefix.</strong><span>Just <code>deploy</code>. The wrapper <em>is</em> the command.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Plain shell, plain YAML.</strong><span>Your script is bash. The manifest is one tiny file. No syntax to fight.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Type-safe.</strong><span>Enum, <code>int</code>, <code>bool</code> params validated before the script runs — bad input fails fast with a structured error.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="compare-row">
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--bad">
              <h3>npm script</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">package.json</span>
                <pre><code>{`"scripts": {
  "deploy": "./scripts/deploy.sh staging"
}`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>$ npm run deploy</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="cons">
                <li><strong>Drags Node into everything.</strong><span>Swift, Go, Rust, Python projects don't want <code>node_modules</code> for shell scripts.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Prefix tax, again.</strong><span><code>npm run deploy</code>, <code>bun run</code>, <code>pnpm run</code> — same five-key tax.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Quoting hell.</strong><span>Single-line JSON strings don't survive multi-line shell scripts cleanly.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-side compare-side--good">
              <h3>Spellbook</h3>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml — works in any project</span>
                <pre><code>{`deploy:
  script: |
    set -e
    echo "deploying…"
    ./deploy.sh staging`}</code></pre>
              </div>
              <div class="snippet">
                <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
                <pre><code>$ deploy
# one binary, zero deps</code></pre>
              </div>
              <ul class="pros">
                <li><strong>One native binary.</strong><span>Single Swift binary on <code>$PATH</code>. No runtime, no <code>node_modules</code>, no version managers.</span></li>
                <li><strong>No prefix.</strong><span>Just <code>deploy</code>. Same UX in Swift, Go, Rust, or a JS repo.</span></li>
                <li><strong>Multi-line scripts, no quoting.</strong><span>YAML block scalars handle <code>set -e</code>, pipes, heredocs — write shell like shell.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="why" aria-label="Why Spellbook">
        <h2>What makes Spellbook different</h2>
        <p class="why__lede">Six things you only get because Spellbook is a real CLI, not a YAML interpreter glued onto a runner.</p>

        <div class="why-grid">
          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">01</span>
              <h3>Fuzzy TAB completion, picker-driven</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Every wrapper gets dynamic TAB completion driven by Spellbook's own <code>/dev/tty</code> picker — fuzzy subsequence matching with highlights, ranked exact → prefix → word-boundary → length, single-digit-millisecond cache hits.</p>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
              <pre><code>{`$ deploy <TAB>          # picker: staging, production, dev
$ deploy st<TAB>        # auto-fills "staging"
$ deploy prd<TAB>       # fuzzy matches "production"
$ deploy --env <TAB>    # second-level enum picker`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">02</span>
              <h3>Shell-escaped placeholders, by default</h3>
            </div>
            <p><code>{'{{name}}'}</code> resolves to a single shell-escaped token. No opt-in, no <code>quote()</code> helpers, no shell-injection footguns when a teammate copy-pastes a script.</p>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml</span>
              <pre><code>{`deploy:
  params:
    env:
    message:
  script: ./deploy {{env}} -m {{message}}`}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">terminal — expanded safely</span>
              <pre><code>{`$ deploy "prod us-east-1" "it's $HOME; rm -rf /"
./deploy 'prod us-east-1' -m 'it'\\''s $HOME; rm -rf /'`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">03</span>
              <h3>Override existing commands safely</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Mark a spell <code>override: true</code> and use <code>{'{{name}}'}</code> to call the real binary. Spellbook resolves it to the next <code>$PATH</code> match outside its own <code>bin/</code> — wrappers can't recurse into themselves.</p>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml</span>
              <pre><code>{`cat:
  override: true
  script: "{{cat}} -n ...args"`}</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
              <pre><code>{`$ cat README.md
# runs /usr/bin/cat -n README.md`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">04</span>
              <h3>Rust/Elm-style structured errors</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Every error has a header, a caret pointing at the problem, body, and a fix tip. Every variant is snapshot-tested. No more <code>bad substitution</code> stack traces.</p>
            <div class="snippet snippet--err">
              <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
              <pre><code>{`$ spells
error: 'git' shadows a PATH binary
   --> spells.yaml:3
   |
 3 |   git:
   |   ^^^
   = note: /usr/bin/git already exists
   = help: add \`override: true\` to confirm`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">05</span>
              <h3>Atomic activation, never half-broken</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Activation is a transaction: validate the full merged manifest, write wrapper temp files, atomically rename, then atomically update state. A bad edit can never strand you with half a working <code>$PATH</code>.</p>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">terminal</span>
              <pre><code>{`$ spells
  ✓ validate spells.yaml + extends chain
  ✓ write 12 wrappers (temp + atomic rename)
  ✓ update state snapshot

  → activated 12 spells from /Users/me/proj`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="why-card">
            <div class="why-card__head">
              <span class="why-card__num">06</span>
              <h3>Silent mode that's actually smart</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Per-spell <code>silent: true</code> shows a spinner in TTY, buffers stdout/stderr, discards on success, flushes on failure. Auto-degrades in CI to plain streaming — no spinner control codes in your logs.</p>
            <div class="snippet">
              <span class="snippet__label">spells.yaml</span>
              <pre><code>{`lint:
  silent: true
